answers.body_markdown:
`v3` is empty when you get to the last loop. `v3.size()` is an unsigned value. So, you are using `0-1` as the upper loop bound, which (in unsigned arithmetic) is a huge value (2&lt;sup&gt;64&lt;/sup&gt;-1 on 64 bit machines).

The simple fix is to not check for `i &lt; v3.size() - 1` but for `i + 1 &lt; v3.size()` as loop bound.

&lt;sup&gt;(The compiler does warn about comparing signed and unsigned values, but even if `i` was unsigned the problem would still occur. You just have to be careful with the corner cases when looping over less than a full container&#39;s size.)&lt;/sup&gt;

